title: Phineas Finn
creator: Anthony Trollope
description: LibriVox recording of Phineas Finn, the Irish Member by Anthony Trollope, read by LibriVox volunteers. Phineas Finn is the sequel to "Can you Forgive Her?" and the second novel in Trollope's Palliser series. The eponymous hero is a young Irishman who becomes a member of the English parliament. Trollope aspired to become an M.P. himself, and he ably describes the workings of the English political scene. There is also a love interest, as the somewhat inconstant Phineas courts three different women: his Irish sweetheart, Mary Flood Jones; Lady Laura Standish, the daughter of a prominent Whig politician; and a lovely heiress, Violet Effingham. (Summary by Karen Merline) This is the second of Trollop's six "Palliser" novels. LibriVox recordings of other novels in the series are available: 1-Can you forgive her? 3-The Eustace Diamonds 4-Phineas Redux 5-The Prime Minister 6-The Duke's Children For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B format available
